Beautiful and very well kept little park, thought for kids and its great! Various playgrounds divided by age groups, the one for the youngest ones is even gated! There's a lawn to sit around or play on the grass as well and since the access is forbidden to dogs (who have their own gated play area) it's clean and poo free!! Recommended!

Awesome park. The main reason we chose our apartment was to be close to it. It has two separate playground areas for kids of different age, one of which subdivides in two for older ages. A huge grass area for picnic, sitting, playing, a modest sport arena in the form of amphitheater, a small separate oval track with soft inclinations where kids can skate, scoot or play with remote controlled vehicles, and yet another separate area for playing with dogs and pets. Easy access from both Mirabeau and Versailles and a nice stone trail around it, including benches on the highest part of the hill that provide a lovely full view of the park.

A large park with both sunny and shaded places to sit.  The sloping grassed areas are popular for sunbathing.  In the centre there is an extensive open area for children to play and playground equipment. The gardens are replanted with colourful flowers several times each year and on either side are un-tended nature zones.

Public park nestled between buildings, sheltered away from the surrounding roads. Large sloping grassed area surrounded by trees and overlooked by the Sainte-Périne geriatric hospital. There are some small decorative gardens. The lawns are open for use including for ball games and picnicking. A gravelled amphitheatre is also popular for ball games. Children's play areas include a sandpit, climbing frames and riding toys for three separate age groups. The paved bike circuit is typically used by young cyclists, skaters and scooters. Dogs on leashes are allowed in certain areas and there is an informal off-leash dog play area. There are several picnic tables and fixed seating scattered around the park. Water fountains are available most of the year (as is the norm with most Parisian parks, water fountains are turned off during winter). Public toilets are outside the rue Mirabeau entrance. There is a park warden. A very popular destination for local families. Not recommended for jogging as to complete a circuit, you must pass through several small swinging gates. Venue for annual summer ball, as organised by the local council (Mairie du 16émé).
